*TITR
X Y and Z are observed from subframes SLAVE_1, SLAVE_2 and SLAVE_3 respectively.
There are 3*7 = 21 degrees of freedom for the three frames - the problem has no solution because there are only 9 observations for 21 degrees of freedom..
By using the SLAVE prefix on the frames, LGC adds constraints:
Helmert parameters of SLAVE_1 = Helmert Parameters of SLAVE_2
and
Helmert parameters of SLAVE_1 = Helmert Parameters of SLAVE_3
(the first SLAVE frame is the master and any other SLAVE frame is forced to have the same helmert parameters)
In the example this introduces 2*7 constraints and the problem becomes solvable: 7 degrees of freedom vs 9 observations.
*OLOC
*CONSI
*APRI
*PREC 6
*INSTR
*CALA
X 1 0 0
Y 0 1 0
Z 0 0 1
*FRAME SLAVE_1 1 2 3 100 20 30 1 TX TY TZ RX RY RZ SCL
*OBSXYZ 
X 1 0 0 6.66 6.66 6.66
*ENDFRAME
*FRAME SLAVE_2 4 5 6 400 40 30 3 TX TY TZ RX RY RZ SCL
*OBSXYZ
Y 0 1 0 6.66 6.66 6.66
*ENDFRAME
*FRAME SLAVE_3 7 8 9 700 800 10 4 TX TY TZ RX RY RZ SCL
*OBSXYZ 
Z 0 0 1 6.66 6.66 6.66 
*ENDFRAME
*END
